This paper deals with word vectors, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of a quantization function, which is a technique used in machine learning for reducing the memory and storage requirements of models. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the quantized word vectors on tasks such as question answering, which could be relevant to categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
